---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms" description="Content license and platform usage." width="narrow">
  <article class="legal">
    <h1>Terms of use</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      learncivicsense.in is a free reading library. The terms below cover content licensing,
      acceptable use, and the limits of what we can promise.
    </p>

    <h2>Content license</h2>
    <p>
      All lessons on this site are published under the
      <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-SA 4.0)
      </a>
      license. You may copy, adapt, and redistribute the lessons, including for commercial purposes, as
      long as you credit learncivicsense.in and share derivatives under the same license.
    </p>

    <h2>Source code</h2>
    <p>
      The website code is open source. See the
      <a href="https://github.com/gragtajar/lcs" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub repository</a>
      for the license that applies to the codebase (separate from the content license above).
    </p>

    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You may read, share, and link to lessons freely.</li>
      <li>You may quote and adapt content under the CC BY-SA 4.0 terms.</li>
      <li>You may not misrepresent the site as your own, or strip attribution.</li>
      <li>You may not deploy automated abuse (scraping at scale that strains the CDN).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>No warranty</h2>
    <p>
      Lessons aim for accuracy and cite their sources, but the site is not professional legal,
      medical, or safety advice. Where a lesson references Indian law or a regulation, treat the
      citation as a pointer to the source, not a final authority.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these terms. The current version is always at this URL with the "last updated"
      date below.
    </p>

    <p class="meta">Last updated: 2026-06-03.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal h1 {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    margin: var(--space-5) 0 var(--space-3);
  }
  .legal h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-2);
  }
  .legal .lede {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }
  .legal p,
  .legal ul {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }
  .legal ul {
    padding-left: var(--space-5);
  }
  .legal li {
    margin-block: var(--space-2);
  }
  .legal .meta {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
  }
</style>
